  <li id="comment-22672" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Hels Bells</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2010/07/summer-list/#comment-22672"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2010-07-05T09:42:10-04:00">Monday, July 5, 2010 at 9:42 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Here in the UK Pimm&#39;s IS summer in a way that no other drink is. My favourite method involves a few hours of forethough but it&#39;s worth it. Take a large jug (you know you&#39;re going to want more than one glass&#8230;) add a handful of chopped strawberries, a touch of sugar and a splash of cointreau and leave for a few hours. Then add orange slices, mint and cucumber then do one part Pimm&#39;s to 3 or 4 parts of 7 Up/Sprite. Then, if you can bear it, wait for an hour or so, add ice and serve.</p>
    </div>

