  <li id="comment-22689" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Anonymous</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2010/07/summer-list/#comment-22689"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2010-07-05T22:10:21-04:00">Monday, July 5, 2010 at 10:10 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I love Pimm&#39;s cup, fell in love with the punch while visiting Cambridge an going on a long walk to King&#39;s Lynn. I make them by the pitcher, as that was how it was served to my friends and I at the pub where we were introduced to the drink. So many people here have a strange taken on it, but how I was told to make them was 1 part Pimms, to 2 parts ginger ale or lemon soda, then add mint, slices of lemon (not orange, it just doesn&#39;t work), halved strawberries an slices of cucumber. I basically add an amount of fruit that is equal to half of the Pimms/soda mixture in the pitcher.</p>
    </div>

