  <li id="comment-22697" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Anonymous</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2010/07/summer-list/#comment-22697"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2010-07-06T05:47:40-04:00">Tuesday, July 6, 2010 at 5:47 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>We had Pimms cup on the 4th of July here in Los Angeles &#8211; it felt right to be drinking a British beverage on the anniversary of us basically flipping them off.  We made a pitcher (pitchers, really) of 1 part Pimms to 2 parts sparkling lemonade (not 7up). Then we loaded up each glass with ice, 1 lemon slice, 1 orange slice, one halved strawberry, 1 slice cucumber (sliced like a pickle) and &#8211; and this is key &#8211; a sprig of mint.  It felt sort of like a dry sangria, really.  They were so good we plan on making it a tradition!</p>
    </div>

      </li><!-- #comment-## -->
