      <a href="https://orangette.net/2010/07/summer-list/#comment-22742"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2010-07-09T19:05:08-04:00">Friday, July 9, 2010 at 7:05 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I&#39;ve found that the absolute key to a proper Pimm&#39;s cup is to use chiffonaded borage leaves in place of cucumbers. They really taste much more like cucumber than cucumbers do. Really delicious, but somewhat hard to find, so we grow our own (they&#39;re also beautiful and as one of your other commentors note, the flowers are edible and look lovely floating about in a cocktail). Cheers!!</p>
    </div>

